        <p><b>Simple - Cut the Crap</b></p>
        <p>The site offers a simple, neutral breakdown of the arguments on both sides of the debate. But we‚Äôve gone through the arguments, on both sides, removed the claims which don‚Äôt stand up to reasonable scrutiny and placed them in a red herrings section - which debunks these arguments. </p>

        <p>The site is interactive, so to explore the details or interrogate our facts, you can just click to delve down into the issues through an explaain bar - which gives further information on issues people care about by breaking down the key elements into short soundbites and linking them together in an intutive manner.</p>

        <p><b>‚Ä¶‚Ä¶..And it's full of emojis!</b> üí° üëå üí™ ‚úå üëä</p>
        <p>
          <i>"We realised that the more the campaigners claim to be giving us 'the facts', the more people don't know who to trust and end up switching off entirely."</i> - Jeremy Evans
        </p>
        <p>
          <i>"If you strip out all the spin then the actual facts are really not that overwhelming. You can learn loads in a couple of minutes - you can read it while you're on the loo."</i> - Jeremy Evans
